    "actor_description": "Nothing is pulling at me. My breath goes all the way down without catching, and my thoughts don't keep grabbing for the next thing. The quiet isn't empty-it's spacious. Shoulders loose. Jaw unclenched. Even my hands feel unhurried, like they've forgotten what it was to brace. I'm just here. Present. Not trying to outrun anything, not trying to force anything. A calm that doesn't need explanation.",
